20systems%20to%20defending%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Justin%20Bronk%2C%20an%20airpower%20expert%2C%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Fdamaged-su-57-emphasises-vulnerability-russian-airbases-near-ukraine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eessay%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20a%20British%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20to%20base%20combat%20aircraft%20is%20always%20a%20dilemma.%20The%20closer%20they%20are%20to%20the%20front%20line%2C%20the%20more%20ordnance%20they%20can%20carry%20rather%20than%20fuel%2C%20and%20less%20time%20is%20wasted%20flying%20back%20and%20forth%20from%20base%20to%20battlefield.%20But%20this%20exposes%20them%20to%20rocket%20and%20drone%20attack%2C%20as%20Ukraine%20demonstrated%20in%202022%20and%202023%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Fmedia-least-24-aircraft-russia-190222156.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrikes%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20Russian%20jets%20and%20helicopters%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20many%20of%20which%20were%20parked%20on%20airfields%20that%20were%20close%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20border%2C%20though%20others%20were%20deeper%20inside%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20were%20pinprick%20attacks%20designed%20to%20embarrass%20the%20Kremlin%20and%20demonstrate%20that%20nowhere%20in%20Russia%20is%20safe%20from%20Ukrainian%20attack.%20Now%2C%20Ukraine%20appears%20to%20be%20systematically%20attacking%20airbases%20with%20drones%2C%20much%20as%20it%20used%20long-range%20American-made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fukraine-says-it-has-destroyed-50-ammunition-depots-using-himars-war-with-russia-2022-07-25%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHIMARS%3C%2Fa%3E%20guided%20rockets%20in%202022%20to%20dismantle%20Russian%20logistic%20and%20command%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetails%20are%20murky%20about%20what%20exactly%20happened%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airforce-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Fsukhoi-su-57-felon-fighter-jet-russia%2F%3Fcf-view%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESu-57%3C%2Fa%3E%20(NATO%20code%20name%3A%20%26quot%3BFelon%26quot%3B)%20stealth%20fighters%20parked%20at%20the%20Akhtubinsk%20airbase%20in%20southern%20Russia%2C%20near%20the%20city%20of%20Volgograd%20(formerly%20Stalingrad)%20and%20about%20370%20miles%20from%20Ukrainian%20territory.%20Ukrainian%20intelligence%20released%20images%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20appeared%20to%20show%20a%20Su-57%20%E2%80%94parked%20in%20the%20open%20%E2%80%94%20that%20was%20allegedly%20damaged%20by%20long-range%20Ukrainian%20drones%2C%20and%20a%20top%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twz.com%2Fair%2Fsu-57-felon-struck-deep-inside-russia-ukraines-spy-agency-claims%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20second%20may%20have%20been%20damaged%20in%20the%20same%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20unclear%20how%20much%20damage%20the%20Su-57%20in%20question%20has%20sustained%2C%26quot%3B%20Bronk%20noted.%20%26quot%3BThe%20satellite%20photo%20appears%20to%20suggest%20that%20two%20relatively%20small%20explosions%20occurred%20within%20around%203%E2%80%935%20meters%20%5B10%20to%2016%20feet%5D%20of%20the%20aircraft%2C%20which%20was%20parked%20on%20an%20outdoor%20concrete%20hardstand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%20didn't%20appear%20to%20catch%20on%20fire%2C%20suggesting%20the%20damage%20wasn't%20catastrophic%2C%20perhaps%20to%20be%20expected%20from%20small%20drones%20with%20small%20warheads.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20plane%20did%20appear%20to%20have%20suffered%20damage%20to%20its%20nose%20and%20tail%2C%20which%20is%20no%20small%20matter%20for%20fragile%20high-performance%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShrapnel%20damage%20to%20the%20rear%20section%20might%20be%20relatively%20easy%20to%20repair%20with%20an%20engine%20change%20and%20replacement%20horizon