p%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJournalist%20Rajat%20Sharma%20moved%20a%20defamation%20suit%20in%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20against%20Congress%20leaders%20on%20Saturday%20and%20sought%20direction%20for%20immediate%20takedown%20of%20the%20posts%20on%20X%20and%20YouTube%20videos%20posted%20by%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Neena%20Bansal%20Krishna%20in%20an%20order%20passed%20on%20June%2014%2C%202024%2C%20stated%20that%20%26quot%3BThe%20irreparable%20loss%20and%20injury%20would%20be%20caused%20to%20the%20plaintiff%2F%20Rajat%20Sharma%20if%20the%20videos%20and%20Tweets%2C%20etc%20as%20mentioned%20above%2C%20are%20allowed%20to%20be%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20it%20would%20continue%20to%20cause%20harm%20to%20his%20reputation%20as%20a%20respectable%20Journalist%20which%20would%20cause%20irreparable%20harm%20to%20the%20plaintiff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20harm%20would%20be%20caused%20to%20the%20defendants%20(Congress%20Leaders%20and%20Social%20Media%20platforms%20)%20if%20the%20material%20is%20restrained%20from%20remaining%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20till%20the%20suit%20is%20adjudicated%20on%20merits%2C%20while%20these%20tweets%20have%20the%20potential%20of%20bringing%20disrepute%20to%20the%20Plaintiff%20in%20future%20with%20practically%20no%20reparation%20to%20the%20damage%20to%20his%20reputation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20plaintiff%20may%20have%20quantified%20damages%20for%20defamation%20and%20to%20his%20reputation%20but%20if%20such%20videos%20are%20permitted%20to%20remain%20in%20public%2C%20the%20harm%20already%20caused%20would%20get%20perpetuated%20in%20future.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20irreparable%20loss%20would%20be%20caused%20to%20the%20applicant%2Fplaintiff%20in%20case%20the%20injunction%20as%20sought%20by%20the%20applicant%2Fplaintiff%20is%20not%20granted%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20directed%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20X%20posts%2FTweets%20which%20have%20not%20been%20remove